        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 7 at 1:59PM MDT by NWS Pocatello ID</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles east of Fort Hall Bannock Peak, or 14 miles west of McCammon,
moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Pocatello, McCammon, Inkom, Portneuf Gap, and Mink Creek
Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
